            <a><h2>Step-by-Step: <br> A Walkthrough My Last Purchase</h2></a>
             <p>The last purchase I made online was for a book on Amazon. 
             <br><br>Quick overview of process: <br>Search Page --> Listings Page --> Product Page --> Cart --> Account Log in --> Order Review Page --> Order Confirmation <br><br>
             **Note: I am not required to log in/confirm my account until I am making a purchase. Otherwise I am signed into my account and it keeps track of my cart. For someone not logged in then they would be redirected/required to log into their account before being able to add items to their cart. 
             <p><a>1)  Navigate </a>to the webpage (www.amazon.ca)
             <p><a>2)  Search: </a>Along the top (header) of the page, to the right of the “amazon.ca” logo, you will see a search bar. With your mouse, click on the blank area of the search bar; doing so will enable you to type in it. Here is where you will type the name of the book you are looking for. You will notice that as you are typing, a dropdown menu will appear with suggestions on what it thinks you are looking for. If you see the item you are looking for, simply use your mouse to click on that item and then skip ahead to the next step. Otherwise, once you have finished typing, feel free to hit enter on your keyboard, or (with your mouse) click on the yellow area with a magnifying glass to the right of the search bar. 
            <p><a>3)  Listings Page:</a> You will see that Amazon returns a bunch of different options based on what it is you typed, and has returned the most relevant items. If it was unable to find a match or relevant information, it will tell you. Return to the search bar from the previous section, and try refining your search. If you entered a long book title, try cutting it down to the main words in the title, or by putting in the author’s name only. <br>Once you have some listings returned, feel free to scroll through them; as you do, notice the options/details for each returned entry. There should be a title, and then details about that specific listing (ex. buying options, shipping information, seller information, reviews, etc.) Personally, once I find one that is relevant to my search, suits my budget and has positive reviews I normally will choose that one. <br>If you feel that this is not sorted to your liking, there are numerous other options. On the top right side of your screen, under your settings (account, wish-list, cart, etc) there is a “Sort by” dropdown menu. You can choose a different way to sort how the returned listings are presented to you (if you so choose). 
             <p><a>4)  The Product Page: </a>Once you have clicked on the listing of your choosing, Amazon will redirect you to the product page. This page will include more information for you to read and review on that specific product. You may be provided with other options or details also. 
             <p><a>5)  Beginning the Checkout Process: </a>If you are satisfied with this listing then you can begin the checkout process (otherwise, go back to the listing page and choose another listing). Along the right side of the window there is square with the purchase information. You may be presented with other options (ex. quantity) for you to choose from. If you are satisfied with the purchasing information, click on the “Add to Cart” yellow button. 
             <p><a>6)  Your Cart: </a> After clicking “Add to Cart” you will be redirected to a page confirming that it has been “Added to Cart”. Here you will see two buttons to choose from. “Cart” will bring you to your shopping cart. If you have added other items to your cart previously, then you will see them all located here. The second option is to “Proceed to checkout”. If you are done shopping, then you can click on this option (for this tutorial we will be choosing this option). 
             <p><a>7)  Account Confirmation: </a>You will be asked to sign in to your account and can click the yellow “Sign in” button. If you do not have an account, then you will have to “Create your Amazon Account” and follow the directions it leads you through. (For the sake of this tutorial we will assume you have an existing account). 
             <p><a>8)  Reviewing and Placing Your Order:</a> Please take a moment on this page to ensure that all the information is correct. You will want to make sure that your Shipping Address, Credit Card info, and the details regarding your purchase are correct. On the right hand side, you will see a breakdown of your Order Summary. If all the information is correct, click on the yellow button to “Place your order” 
             <p><a>9)  Congratulations! </a>You have now purchased an item and successfully completed an order. It may take a few moments for Amazon to confirm the purchase; make sure not to refresh your page while waiting. You should see an order confirmation with an order number for your records. You should also receive an emailed copy confirming your transaction (I always like to jot down the order number confirmation regardless, just to be safe!) . If you are encountered with an issue and your order was not completed, please follow the steps that Amazon is giving you. Otherwise, feel free to navigate away from the page and enjoy your purchase! 
             </p>
